{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0b86a2d4-b79c-48b5-b97b-de13a69d003a","content":"Analyzing .dmp files is outside the scope of the tools I have here (the `dump-collect` skill covers **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them). However, here's how you can investigate:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the session:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `pe` | Print last exception (start here!) |\n| `threads` | List managed threads |\n| `setthread <id>` | Switch to a thread |\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n| `gcroot <addr>` | Trace object roots |\n\n**Using Visual Studio** (Windows):\n- Open the `.dmp` file directly → click **Debug with Managed Only**.\n\n**Using `lldb`** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nsos PrintException\n```\n\nStart with `pe` (PrintException) — it usually points straight to the crash cause. Want help interpreting the output?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5c6247ce-1221-4ae7-8f36-e61a51d26189","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for **collecting** crash dumps, and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":414,"requestId":"9444:164D4D:197CD26:1CDFACC:69E82172"},"id":"006e20a3-f431-4dc6-9b40-5997723e9341","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:16:47.895Z","parentId":"6873519a-8e00-4227-8c5f-428a8e1fcd18"}
